''Lombard RAC Rally'''s developers ([[Red Rat Software]]) also released a superficially similar game called ''Speed Run'' for [[Atari 8-bit computers]]<ref name='atarimania-8'>{{cite web|url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-speed-run_4893.html|title=Atari 400 800 XL XE Speed Run: scans, dump, download, screenshots, ads, videos, catalog, instructions, roms|website=Atarimania.com|accessdate=31 December 2018}}</ref> with the same animated driver, but more simplistic through-the-window graphics and gameplay. Early adverts for ''Speed Run'' also mentioned an Atari ST version,<ref>{{cite journal | url=https://archive.org/details/Page_6_Issue_31_1988-01_ABACUS_GB/page/n1 | date = January 1988 | journal = [[Page 6| Page 6 Atari Users Magazine]] | issue = 31 | pages = 2 | title = Speed Run (advertisement) | publisher = [[Page 6|Page 6 Publishing]]}}</ref> but do not make clear whether that proposed version later evolved into ''Lombard RAC Rally'' instead.

